President Trump delivered remarks at the White House honoring the Cuban-American veterans of the Bay of Pigs Invasion. He expressed his gratitude for their endorsement and support, and reaffirmed the United States' commitment to a free Cuba. The President announced new sanctions on Cuba, Venezuela, and Nicaragua, and stated that the United States will not lift sanctions until certain conditions are met, such as the release of political prisoners and the scheduling of free elections. He also emphasized his administration's efforts to defend religious liberty and the right to life, and highlighted the economic achievements of Hispanic Americans. Several veterans and politicians spoke at the event, expressing their support for the President and their commitment to fighting against socialism and communism. The President concluded by stating that Cuba will soon be free and that the United States will continue to defend freedom and the American way of life.